data.description: Charmingly Spectacular!  Location, Location, Location!  Welcome home to your unique one of a kind charming home built in 1910.  Mankin’s Cottage Grove named after Ms. Elma Mankin, owner of this signature home in this distinct development.  Walking distance to Herndon's Downtown Historic District.  Bright & open offering an abundance of natural light.    Relish in the exceptional character and original particulars throughout the home; Hardwood floors refinished to their original beauty.  Built-in window nooks, book cases, shelving and cabinetry at every turn.  Generous sized front porch (approximately 320 sqft) is perfect for entertaining or just enjoying the cool Summer breeze or watching the autumn leaves blow.  The 2nd floor balcony (approximately, 32 sqft) overlooking quiet Stanton Park across the street. The side yard features a slate patio.  The rear yard features a concrete patio, perfect for grilling and dining outside or making s'more's on a fire pit.  Notable updates and renovations include; new roof (2023), new insulation in the attic (2023), refinished hardwood floors (2023), kitchen upgrades (2023), fresh paint (2023), New carpet in 4th bedroom Loft (2023) and an oversized 2 car detached garage with an abundance of shelving and storage and 4th bedroom Loft and full bathroom (2016) perfect for In-laws or an Au Pair.    Both fireplaces are non-functional (as-is) and considered decorative only.  This property is NOT in the Herndon Historic Preservation District (HDRB)  This family neighborhood is conveniently located next to the Herndon Recreation Community Pool.  And only minutes from Downtown Herndon featuring restaurants, bars, coffee shops, salons, library and the W&OD Trail.  And a quick jaunt away from Reston Town Center, Dulles Airport and the Silver Line Metro stops.
